---

Read AGENTS.md before doing anything in this repo. Summary of the parts that are
easy to get wrong:

- Build with `python scripts/build.py resume.yaml --format pdf,docx,txt --check`.
  Never hand-write resume HTML — the templates encode measured constraints.
- ALWAYS run `python scripts/ats_check.py Resume.pdf --data resume.yaml` and report
  the result. Never claim "ATS-friendly" without it.
- Single column only. Measured: side-by-side blocks merge into fabricated lines at
  PDF extraction ("Senior Engineer, Acme  Python, Go"). DOM order does not fix it —
  PDF has no DOM. Tables are the worst offender, not the safe choice.
- No skill bars/dots/stars, no contact icons, no photo (US/UK/CA/AU).
- Never invent employers, titles, dates, degrees, or metrics.
- Numbers live in assets/tokens.css. Never hard-code them in a template.
- 107 named looks: `--list-presets`, `--preset <name>`, `scripts/gallery.py`.
